      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not just about \"diverse perspectives\" though. it's about the actual mechanics of how they do it. if a group like the UN or the WEF decides a certain truth is too dangerous for the public to know, they don't just disagree with it, they erase it from the digital record entirely. if we can't trust the archives because the people in charge of them are the ones with the most to hide, then what's the point of even studying history? how can we be sure any of the \"official\" records haven't been scrubbed to protect their interests?",
